<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>How does an increase in the reserve requirement affect the money supply?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Increases the money supply by increasing bank lending</option>
            <option letter="b">Decreases the money supply by reducing bank lending</option>
            <option letter="c">Has no effect on the money supply</option>
            <option letter="d">Only affects the money supply during recessions</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>When the Fed increases the reserve requirement, banks must hold more reserves against deposits, leaving less money available for lending. This reduces the money multiplier and decreases the money supply as banks can create less money through the lending process.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
